Quote: During the month of July, 1924, Wellington harbour was visited by an enormous shoal of pilchards, or sardines (<i>Sardinia neopilchardus</i>). ... This fish is identical with the well-known `Picton herring', which is sold in a smoked condition every winter in Wellington.
