Edition:
Quote: With regard to its popular names, [the New Zealand sprat] has frequently been referred to as the Pilchard, New Zealand Herring, and by other local names. <i>Ibid.</i> 29 THE PILCHARD <i>Sardinia neopichardus</i> (<i>Steindachner</i>) ... Maori name: MOHIMOHI. <i>Ibid.</i> 169 Pilchard Sardinops neopilchardus Sardine; Picton Herring (Syn. <i>Clupea lata</i> Richardson)
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1986
Source: NZ Fishes: An Identification Guide
Author: PAUL
Vol / Page: 40
Edition:
Quote: <i>Pilchard Sardinops neopilchardus</i> ... Sometimes called the sardine. Also occurs around southern Australia. ... In the 1880s a fishery in the Marlborough Sounds produced salted and smoked `Picton Herring', and small fisheries have developed briefly elsewhere. ... Pilchard are caught for groper bait (`bloater'), and have been used also for tuna.
Notes:

